<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/68493135-yun-choi"><img alt="" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_100x100-259587f1619f5253426a4fa6fb508831.png" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/68493135-yun-choi">Yun Choi</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">I believe that Amy Tan represents her mom, Winny, as a Kitchen God&apos;s wife. In the story, Winny tells her daughter about Kitchen God. The Kitchen God i<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">I believe that Amy Tan represents her mom, Winny, as a Kitchen God's wife. In the story, Winny tells her daughter about Kitchen God. The Kitchen God is no better than human. It actually worse. You don't even want to call as a God. But he is a still God. Winny married a crazy bad man in her first marriage. It seems represents that crazy man as a God and Kitchen wife is Winny herself. <a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerFooter'>

