<div id="review_1077717174" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1077717174" />
    <a title="Carol She&#39;s So Novel꧁꧂ " class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/25867535-carol-she-s-so-novel"><img alt="Carol She&#39;s So Novel꧁꧂ " src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1613262129p2/25867535.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1077717174?book_show_action=true">Oct 11, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Carol She&#39;s So Novel꧁꧂ " class="user" itemprop="url" name="Carol She&#39;s So Novel꧁꧂ " href="/user/show/25867535-carol-she-s-so-novel">Carol She&#39;s So Novel꧁꧂ </a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780006545064" href="/book/show/1079968.The_Kitchen_God_s_Wife">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/25867535-carol-she-s-so-novel?shelf=historical">historical</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/25867535-carol-she-s-so-novel?shelf=through-the-generations">through-the-generations</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1077717174" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6461245511825250648">&quot;It&apos;s not you it&apos;s me&quot; is what I feel like saying to this book!<br/><br/>It hit a couple of tender spots for me at the start because of my own mother/daughter relationship. I put aside for a while because I found the switch in POV to the mother a bit hard to handle. It was rhetorical whining really &amp; the story was uniformly depressing. I had to keep taking breaks &amp; read something else.<br/><br/>I&apos;m unlikely to read anything else by this author.</span>
  <span id="freeText6461245511825250648" style="display:none">"It's not you it's me" is what I feel like saying to this book!<br /><br />It hit a couple of tender spots for me at the start because of my own mother/daughter relationship. I put aside for a while because I found the switch in POV to the mother a bit hard to handle. It was rhetorical whining really &amp; the story was uniformly depressing. I had to keep taking breaks &amp; read something else.<br /><br />I'm unlikely to read anything else by this author.</span>
  <a data-text-id="6461245511825250648" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


